{"parse":{"title":"Speech shadowing","pageid":22434851,"revid":831445640,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b>Speech shadowing</b> is an experimental technique in which subjects <a href=\"/wiki/Speech_repetition\" title=\"Speech repetition\">repeat speech</a> immediately after hearing it (usually through <a href=\"/wiki/Earphones\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Earphones\">earphones</a>). The <a href=\"/wiki/Reaction_time\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Reaction time\">reaction time</a> between hearing a word and <a href=\"/wiki/Pronunciation\" title=\"Pronunciation\">pronouncing</a> it can be as short as 254 ms<sup id=\"cite_ref-Marslen_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Marslen-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> or even 150 ms.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Chistovich_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Chistovich-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> This is only the delay duration of a speech <a href=\"/wiki/Syllable\" title=\"Syllable\">syllable</a>. While a person is only asked to repeat words, they also automatically process their <a href=\"/wiki/Syntax\" title=\"Syntax\">syntax</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Semantics\" title=\"Semantics\">semantics</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Marslen_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Marslen-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> Words repeated during the practice of shadowing imitate the parlance of the overheard words more than the same words read aloud by that subject.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> The technique is also used in <a href=\"/wiki/Language_learning\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Language learning\">language learning</a>.\n</p><p><a href=\"/wiki/Functional_imaging\" title=\"Functional imaging\">Functional imaging</a> finds that the shadowing of <a href=\"/wiki/Nonword\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Nonword\">nonwords</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> occurs through the dorsal stream that links auditory and motor representations of speech through a pathway that starts in the <a href=\"/wiki/Superior_temporal_gyrus\" title=\"Superior temporal gyrus\">superior temporal cortex</a>, goes to the <a href=\"/wiki/Inferior_parietal_lobule\" title=\"Inferior parietal lobule\">inferior parietal cortex</a> and then the <a href=\"/wiki/Inferior_frontal_gyrus\" title=\"Inferior frontal gyrus\">posterior inferior frontal cortex</a> (<a href=\"/wiki/Broca%27s_area\" title=\"Broca&#39;s area\">Broca's area</a>).<sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Speech shadowing was first used as a research technique by the Leningrad Group led by <a href=\"/wiki/Ludmilla_A.Chistovich\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Ludmilla A.Chistovich\">Ludmilla A.Chistovich</a> in the late 1950s.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Chistovich_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Chistovich-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> It has been used in research into <a href=\"/wiki/Speech_perception\" title=\"Speech perception\">speech perception</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Marslen_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Marslen-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> and <a href=\"/wiki/Stuttering\" title=\"Stuttering\">stuttering</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Experimental_applications\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Experimental applications</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#See_also\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">See also</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Footnotes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Footnotes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Bibliography\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Bibliography</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Experimental_applications\">Experimental applications</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Speech_shadowing&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Experimental applications\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The speech shadowing technique is used in <a href=\"/wiki/Dichotic_listening_tests\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Dichotic listening tests\">dichotic listening tests</a>. The first one to apply this technique was E. Colin Cherry in 1953.<sup id=\"cite_ref-FOOTNOTECherry1953976_8-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-FOOTNOTECherry1953976-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup> During dichotic listening tests, subjects are presented with two different messages, one in their right ear and one in their left. The participants are often asked to focus on only one of the different messages and this is where the speech shadowing technique is used. Participants are instructed to shadow the attended message by repeating it out loud with a delay of a few seconds between hearing a word and repeating the word. The speech shadowing technique is significant for these experiments because it ensures that the subjects are attending to the desired message.<sup id=\"cite_ref-9\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup> Various other stimuli are then presented to the other ear, and subjects are afterwards queried on what they can recall from the other message.<sup id=\"cite_ref-FOOTNOTECherry1953977-979_10-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-FOOTNOTECherry1953977-979-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Speech_shadowing&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Cohort_model\" title=\"Cohort model\">Cohort model</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Mirror_neurons\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Mirror neurons\">Mirror neurons</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Psycholinguistics\" title=\"Psycholinguistics\">Psycholinguistics</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Footnotes\">Footnotes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Speech_shadowing&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Footnotes\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist columns references-column-width\" style=\"-moz-column-width: 30em; -webkit-column-width: 30em; column-width: 30em; list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Marslen-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-Marslen_1-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-Marslen_1-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-Marslen_1-2\"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation journal\">Marslen-Wilson, W. (1973). \"Linguistic structure and speech shadowing at very short latencies\". <i>Nature</i>. <b>244</b> (5417): 522\u2013523. <a href=\"/wiki/Digital_object_identifier\" title=\"Digital object identifier\">doi</a>:<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"//doi.org/10.1038/244522a0\">10.1038/244522a0</a>. <a href=\"/wiki/PubMed_Identifier\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"PubMed Identifier\">PMID</a>&#160;<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"//www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/4621131\">4621131</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Nature&amp;rft.atitle=Linguistic+structure+and+speech+shadowing+at+very+short+latencies&amp;rft.volume=244&amp;rft.issue=5417&amp;rft.pages=522-523&amp;rft.date=1973&amp;rft_id=info%3Adoi%2F10.1038%2F244522a0&amp;rft_id=info%3Apmid%2F4621131&amp;rft.aulast=Marslen-Wilson&amp;rft.aufirst=W.&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ASpeech+shadowing\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Chistovich-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-Chistovich_2-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-Chistovich_2-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation journal\">Marslen-Wilson, W. D. (1985). \"Speech shadowing and speech comprehension\". <i>Speech Communication</i>. <b>4</b>: 55\u201373. <a href=\"/wiki/Digital_object_identifier\" title=\"Digital object identifier\">doi</a>:<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"//doi.org/10.1016/0167-6393%2885%2990036-6\">10.1016/0167-6393(85)90036-6</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Speech+Communication&amp;rft.atitle=Speech+shadowing+and+speech+comprehension&amp;rft.volume=4&amp;rft.pages=55-73&amp;rft.date=1985&amp;rft_id=info%3Adoi%2F10.1016%2F0167-6393%2885%2990036-6&amp;rft.aulast=Marslen-Wilson&amp;rft.aufirst=W.+D.&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ASpeech+shadowing\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation journal\">Shockley, K.; Sabadini, L.; Fowler, C. A. (2004). \"Imitation in shadowing words\". <i>Perception &amp; Psychophysics</i>. <b>66</b> (3): 422\u2013429. <a href=\"/wiki/Digital_object_identifier\" title=\"Digital object identifier\">doi</a>:<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"//doi.org/10.3758/BF03194890\">10.3758/BF03194890</a>. <a href=\"/wiki/PubMed_Identifier\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"PubMed Identifier\">PMID</a>&#160;<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"//www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/15283067\">15283067</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Perception+%26+Psychophysics&amp;rft.atitle=Imitation+in+shadowing+words&amp;rft.volume=66&amp;rft.issue=3&amp;rft.pages=422-429&amp;rft.date=2004&amp;rft_id=info%3Adoi%2F10.3758%2FBF03194890&amp;rft_id=info%3Apmid%2F15283067&amp;rft.aulast=Shockley&amp;rft.aufirst=K.&amp;rft.au=Sabadini%2C+L.&amp;rft.au=Fowler%2C+C.+A.&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ASpeech+shadowing\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://app.psychonomic-journals.org/content/66/3/422.full.pdf\">PDF</a><sup class=\"noprint Inline-Template\"><span style=\"white-space: nowrap;\">&#91;<i><a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Link_rot\" title=\"Wikipedia:Link rot\"><span title=\"&#160;Dead link since March 2018\">permanent dead link</span></a></i>&#93;</span></sup></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation journal\">Peschke, C.; Ziegler, W.; Kappes, J.; Baumgaertner, A. (2009). \"Auditory\u2013motor integration during fast repetition: The neuronal correlates of shadowing\". <i>NeuroImage</i>. <b>47</b> (1): 392\u2013402. <a href=\"/wiki/Digital_object_identifier\" title=\"Digital object identifier\">doi</a>:<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"//doi.org/10.1016/j.neuroimage.2009.03.061\">10.1016/j.neuroimage.2009.03.061</a>. <a href=\"/wiki/PubMed_Identifier\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"PubMed Identifier\">PMID</a>&#160;<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"//www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/19345269\">19345269</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=NeuroImage&amp;rft.atitle=Auditory%E2%80%93motor+integration+during+fast+repetition%3A+The+neuronal+correlates+of+shadowing&amp;rft.volume=47&amp;rft.issue=1&amp;rft.pages=392-402&amp;rft.date=2009&amp;rft_id=info%3Adoi%2F10.1016%2Fj.neuroimage.2009.03.061&amp;rft_id=info%3Apmid%2F19345269&amp;rft.aulast=Peschke&amp;rft.aufirst=C.&amp;rft.au=Ziegler%2C+W.&amp;rft.au=Kappes%2C+J.&amp;rft.au=Baumgaertner%2C+A.&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ASpeech+shadowing\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-5\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation journal\">Hickok, G.; Poeppel, D. (2004). \"Dorsal and ventral streams: A framework for understanding aspects of the functional anatomy of language\". <i>Cognition</i>. <b>92</b> (1\u20132): 67\u201399. <a href=\"/wiki/Digital_object_identifier\" title=\"Digital object identifier\">doi</a>:<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"//doi.org/10.1016/j.cognition.2003.10.011\">10.1016/j.cognition.2003.10.011</a>. <a href=\"/wiki/PubMed_Identifier\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"PubMed Identifier\">PMID</a>&#160;<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"//www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/15037127\">15037127</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Cognition&amp;rft.atitle=Dorsal+and+ventral+streams%3A+A+framework+for+understanding+aspects+of+the+functional+anatomy+of+language&amp;rft.volume=92&amp;rft.issue=1%E2%80%932&amp;rft.pages=67-99&amp;rft.date=2004&amp;rft_id=info%3Adoi%2F10.1016%2Fj.cognition.2003.10.011&amp;rft_id=info%3Apmid%2F15037127&amp;rft.aulast=Hickok&amp;rft.aufirst=G.&amp;rft.au=Poeppel%2C+D.&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ASpeech+shadowing\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-6\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-6\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation journal\">Chistovich, L. A.; Pickett, J. M.; Porter, R. J. (1998). \"Speech research at the I. P. Pavlov Institute in Leningrad/St. Petersburg\". <i>The Journal of the Acoustical Society of America</i>. <b>103</b> (5): 3024. <a href=\"/wiki/Digital_object_identifier\" title=\"Digital object identifier\">doi</a>:<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"//doi.org/10.1121/1.422540\">10.1121/1.422540</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=The+Journal+of+the+Acoustical+Society+of+America&amp;rft.atitle=Speech+research+at+the+I.+P.+Pavlov+Institute+in+Leningrad%2FSt.+Petersburg&amp;rft.volume=103&amp;rft.issue=5&amp;rft.pages=3024&amp;rft.date=1998&amp;rft_id=info%3Adoi%2F10.1121%2F1.422540&amp;rft.aulast=Chistovich&amp;rft.aufirst=L.+A.&amp;rft.au=Pickett%2C+J.+M.&amp;rft.au=Porter%2C+R.+J.&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ASpeech+shadowing\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-7\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-7\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation journal\">Harbison Jr, D. C.; Porter Jr, R. J.; Tobey, E. A. (1989). \"Shadowed and simple reaction times in stutterers and nonstutterers\". <i>The Journal of the Acoustical Society of America</i>. <b>86</b> (4): 1277\u